definition: to cross/to go over/to pass (time)/to celebrate (a holiday)/to live/to get along/excessively/too-
many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"

sentences.english: Memory allocation failures should reduce the use of this flag.
sentences.chinese: 如果内存分配失败过多，应该减少这个标记的使用。

sentences.english: I don't like too much plot , because I prefer things to be character-driven.
sentences.chinese: 我不喜欢过多的情节，因为我喜欢由人物推动的故事。

sentences.english: Do not clutter up the page with so many illustrations that you obscure the message.
sentences.chinese: 不要在一页内放置过多的插图，那样会模糊讯息。

sentences.english: It is well-known that lung cancer is caused at least in part by smoking too much.
sentences.chinese: 众所周知，肺癌至少部分是由于吸烟过多引起的。

sentences.english: There’s no doubt that law schools have overbuilt and that the legal profession has overpromised.
sentences.chinese: 毫无疑问，法学院过多了，并对法定职业夸下海口。

sentences.english: He didn't explain so much but came to the point.
sentences.chinese: 他没有过多的解释但却击中要害。

sentences.english: It is well-known that cancer at least partly caused by over smoking.
sentences.chinese: 众所周知，肺癌至少部分地是由于吸烟过多引起的。

sentences.english: With an excess of carbon dioxide, Venus is hot enough to melt lead.
sentences.chinese: 而二氧化碳过多的话，金星可以热到能融化铅的地步。

sentences.english: These effects of excess androgens are called virilization and occur rarely.
sentences.chinese: 这些过多雄激素的影响即罕见的女性男性化。

sentences.english: The excessive or insufficient silt-content is unfavorable to the vibrating consolidation of sandy soils.
sentences.chinese: 粉粒含量过多或太少均不利于砂土的振动固结。

sentences.english: The inventory showed that the store was overstocked.
sentences.chinese: 清单显示商店存货过多。

sentences.english: Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is defined as a syndrome of ovarian hyperandrogenism and chronic anovulation.
sentences.chinese: 多囊卵巢综合征以雄激素过多和持续无排卵为特征。

sentences.english: Too much  perming and coloring can be harmful.
sentences.chinese: 过多的烫发和染发会对发质造成损害。

sentences.english: The reason why one is fat is partly caused by overeating.
sentences.chinese: 造成肥胖的部分原因是饮食过多。

sentences.english: There wasn't a lot of focus on vocabulary or grammar.
sentences.chinese: 训练课并没有过多注重词汇量和语法的学习。

definition: few/less/to lack/to be missing/to stop (doing sth)/seldom
